 part: he was surrounded by rough boys who disliked him intensely and there was nothing to prevent their pulling his magic instrument to pieces. But there he sat coolly transcribing some text and explaining in his high-pitched drawl the niceties of the demonstration. Schimpffer, a red-haired boy of Alsatian descent, with extremely efficient fingers, said: 'Now let me try!' and Paduk made room for him and directed his — at first somewhat suspensive — taps. Krug tried next, and Paduk helped hi